section.section:
An officer of a nonprofit health service plan shall act:
in good faith;
in a manner that is reasonably believed to be in the best interests of the corporation and its controlled affiliates or subsidiaries that offer health benefit plans;
in a manner that is consistent with the mission of a nonprofit health service plan as required under § 14-102(c) of this subtitle; and
with the care that an ordinarily prudent person in a like position would use under similar circumstances.
